              "state": "COMMENTED",
              "body": "## Code Review\n\nThis pull request migrates the project's component library from Storybook to React Cosmos, which includes updating dependencies, scripts, and converting existing stories into fixtures. Other notable changes include upgrading the Node.js engine requirement to version 24, switching to Vite's native tsconfig path resolution, and refining the PostgreSQL error detection logic. Feedback is provided regarding the `jscpd` configuration, which currently ignores all `.tsx` files; this should be narrowed to only ignore fixture files to ensure that core component logic remains subject to copy-paste detection.",
              "author": { "login": "gemini-code-assist" },
              "comments": {
                "nodes": [
                  {
                    "id": "PRRC_kwDOSTMPFs69zzr-",
                    "body": "![medium](https://www.gstatic.com/codereviewagent/medium-priority.svg)\n\nThe `jscpd` configuration ignores all `.tsx` files from copy-paste detection. This is very broad and will prevent detection of duplicated code in your actual React components. This is likely not the intended behavior.\n\nIf the goal is to ignore component fixtures (which often contain boilerplate), it would be better to use a more specific pattern that targets only fixture files, like `\"**/*.fixture.tsx\"`.\n\n```suggestion\n      \"**/*.fixture.tsx\",\n```",
